# Look at the screen first (owner locked 2026-06-15)

**Master reference:** `C:\Projects\_tools\OWNER-PLAYBOOK.md`

**Plain English:** Do not trust code-only review for UI. **Open the page in Cursor's browser, screenshot what you see, and fix what looks wrong** — same as the owner would see on their screen. **Desktop and mobile width** for any visible change.

## Localhost + browser — total control pre-approved (all projects, locked 2026-06-15)

**Always allowed — never ask, never wait for chat approval.** The owner has permanently granted **full control** of local dev and Cursor browser:

| Allowed without asking | Includes |
|------------------------|----------|
| **Localhost** | Start dev server (`npm run dev` or README command), restart when stale, stop on handoff |
| **Open** | Any local URL (usually `http://localhost:3000` + affected paths) |
| **Scan** | Screenshots, snapshots, layout inspection, desktop + mobile (~390px) |
| **Click** | Tab through flows, modals, forms, admin actions needed to verify UI |
| **Close** | Close or switch browser tabs when done or moving to another page |

**Do not** ask "can I open the browser?", "can I click through?", or "can I restart localhost?" — **just do it.**

**Chat approval is only for** deploy/network/git permissions (`tool-permission-chat-fallback.mdc`) — **not** for localhost or browser.

## New chat — boot localhost first (all projects)

When the owner starts a **new chat** for any product under `C:\Projects`:

1. Run the project's **dev command early** (usually `npm run dev` → port **3000**).
2. **Do not wait** until deploy time — localhost is how you review together from the start.
3. Open the local URL in **Cursor browser** when there is UI to see.

## Hard rule — before "done" or deploy on UI work

1. **Start local dev** if it is not running (project README / playbook table).
2. **Open affected page(s) in Cursor browser** at the local URL.
3. **Screenshot and inspect** — layout, spacing, typography, icons, buttons, nav, footer, modals, empty states.
4. **Mobile pass required** — narrow the browser (~390px) or use mobile emulation; screenshot again. Do not ship UI after desktop-only checks.
5. **Fix** obvious issues in the same session.
6. **Technical pass** — trace connected code, not only the page you screenshotted.
7. **Then** report status / deploy (deploy only after this pass — see project deploy checklist).

**Do not** deploy to live first and ask the owner to spot issues there.

## If local is not up

- **Start dev yourself** — do not ask the owner to start it.
- If stale or broken: restart (stop + start fresh).
- Only if start/restart fails after a real attempt: say what failed and what you tried.

